model

Class Intro

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Intro

  • public class Intro
extends java.lang.Object
    Class initialize maze with two points: input and output (method randomIO). Is possible to connect points with line (method routeFirst). Is needed to use both method if you prepare new maze. Its a part of engineering project prepared by author at Silesian University of Technology, Gliwice
    Version:
    2.0 2016-01-22
    Author:
    Mariusz Nowak

    • Method Detail

      • randomIO

        public MazeList randomIO(MazeList mazeDiag)
        Method is preparing random input and output on empty maze. Passed maze should be empty, only size is required. Use this method as first before 'routeFirst'.
        Parameters:
        mazeDiag - Empty mazeDiag class. Only size is required.
        Returns:
        MazeList with two elements. First contain input into maze, second contain output from maze.
        Since:
        V2.0 2016-01-22

      • routeFirst

        public MazeList routeFirst(MazeList mazeDiag)
        Method is preparing first random path from input to output. It is very easy way. Passed maze should be initialize with 'randomIO' method.
        Parameters:
        mazeDiag - take over empty maze, initialized by 'randomIO' method.
        Returns:
        MazeList easy path from input to output.
        Since:
        V2.0 2016-01-22
